name: WormArt - Invasion
description:
Original photography fed to the ravenous Algorithm Worms which secrete a delightful pigment trail as they happily writhe around the canvas.

The 26th of January can be a contentious day in Australia. It is the holiday which is used to commemorate the landing of the First Fleet in 1788, but is also a reminder to First Nations people and others of the genocide and displacement that followed. This photo comes from one of the local fireworks displays that are run in many cities around the country on the evening of the 26th.

3000x3000.
